    Verse: 1
Tags:
  - Death
---
Death is only pushing aside the portiere and passing from one room to
another. ... I think of death as a glad awakening from this troubled sleep
which we call life; as an emancipation from the world which, beautiful though
it be, is still a land of captivity.
